# Testing Standards

## Test file locations and naming

| Source file | Test file |
|---|---|
| `src/client/components/<Foo>.tsx` | `src/client/components/__tests__/<Foo>.test.tsx` |
| `src/client/hooks/<bar>.ts` | `src/client/hooks/__tests__/<bar>.test.ts` |
| `src/client/utils/<baz>.ts` | `src/client/utils/__tests__/<baz>.test.ts` |
| `src/server/services/<svc>.ts` | `src/server/__tests__/<svc>.test.ts` |
| `src/server/routes/<route>.ts` | `src/server/__tests__/<route>Routes.test.ts` |

## Structure

Every test file must have:

- At least one `describe` block per exported function or component
- Each `describe` contains a happy-path test and at least one error or edge-case test
- Mocks declared at the top of the file via `jest.mock(...)` before any `describe` blocks

```ts
jest.mock('../../services/myService', () => ({
  doThing: jest.fn(),
}));

describe('MyComponent', () => {
  it('renders correctly with valid props', () => { ... });
  it('shows an error state when the query fails', () => { ... });
});
```

## What tests must cover

- Only the **new** feature behaviour introduced by the current change
- Do not write tests that assert on existing page structure, existing sidebar items, or navigation behaviour unrelated to the feature

## Mocking conventions

- Mock all external I/O: API calls (`fetch`), ADO client, file system, database
- Use `jest.fn()` and `mockResolvedValue` / `mockRejectedValue` — never real network or DB calls in unit tests
- Reset mocks in `beforeEach` using `jest.clearAllMocks()`

## React component tests

- Use `@testing-library/react` (`render`, `screen`, `fireEvent`, `waitFor`)
- Wrap components in a `MemoryRouter` if they use `useNavigate` / `useLocation`
- Wrap in `QueryClientProvider` with `retry: false` if they use TanStack Query hooks
- Prefer `getByRole` queries; use `getByText` or `getByTestId` only when role queries are ambiguous

## TypeScript in tests

- Test files must be `.test.ts` or `.test.tsx` — match the source file extension
- Do not use `any` casts to silence type errors; fix the type issue instead
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` with the relevant tsconfig after writing tests to catch compilation errors

## Running tests

```bash
# Run a single test file
npx jest <path-to-test-file> --passWithNoTests

# Run the full suite
npm test
```

Fix all failures before committing. Do not skip tests with `.skip` or `.only` in committed code.
